user_message:
An agent A claimed that the following MHD_set_connection_value_n code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 21.17.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17 is Use of the string handling functions from <string.h> shall not result in accesses beyond the bounds of the objects referenced by their pointer parameters.
This rule strictly applies to the Standard Library functions in <string.h> such as memcpy, memmove, memset, memcmp, strcpy, strncpy, strcat, strncat, strlen, and strspn.
</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of MHD_set_connection_value_n.
```c
_MHD_EXTERN enum MHD_Result
MHD_set_connection_value_n (struct MHD_Connection *connection,
                            enum MHD_ValueKind kind,
                            const char *key,
                            size_t key_size,
                            const char *value,
                            size_t value_size)
{
  if ( (MHD_GET_ARGUMENT_KIND != kind) &&
       ( ((key ? strlen (key) : 0) != key_size) ||
         ((value ? strlen (value) : 0) != value_size) ) )
    return MHD_NO; /* binary zero is allowed only in GET arguments */

  return MHD_set_connection_value_n_nocheck_ (connection,
                                              kind,
                                              key,
                                              key_size,
                                              value,
                                              value_size);
}
```
</target_code>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- explanation: your evaluation of the scenario provided by the agent A.
- is_report_correct: whether the report is correct or not (true/false). True means there is a violation.
</response format>
<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. The code calls strlen(key) and strlen(value) whenever key/value != NULL. If the caller supplies a non-NULL pointer that is not NUL-terminated but is accompanied by an explicit size (key_size/value_size) — e.g. a 3-byte buffer {'a','b','c'} with key_size==3 and no terminating '\0' — strlen will read past the provided buffer looking for a NUL byte. For kind != MHD_GET_ARGUMENT_KIND this check will execute and can access beyond the bounds of the objects, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
